Bank of Nova Scotia said Chief
Executive Officer Rick Waugh will retire Nov. 1 and be replaced
by Brian Porter.  Waugh will stay on the board and become deputy chairman
until Jan. 31, 2014, the Toronto-based lender said today in a
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
